Source:  Bungalow in New Zealand, The
Author:  ASHFORD
Vol / Page:  46
Edition:
Quote:  These included 'Konka' which had been patented in 195 by R.M. Mander of Palmerston North, and consisted of a backing board (3ft x 2ft x 5/8in) for stucco made from cement, fibres and pumice... The popularity of Konka later increased and it was advertised nationally in the 1930s.
