Quote:  in New Zealand stucco was applied directly to sheet materials such as asbestos cement, - two local products - Konka board and Gibraltar

sheathing and a variety of imitations.... Konka was first used in Wanganui in 1912 as a patented concrete sheet 91cm x 76cm by 15 mm thick.
